Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Bolivia. The Bolivian authorities have introduced a number of measures to limit the spread of the virus.
International travel
All international and domestic flights will be suspended from 0000h on 21 March. All borders will close to new arrivals by 20 March. Entry will be \ermitted for Bolivian nationals and foreign residents in Bolivia only.
We strongly encourage non-resident British nationals in Bolivia to consider leaving to avoid difficulties they will face if flights out of the country and the region are further restricted and they are unable to get home. Should you wish to leave and are unable, please register your contact details with the Consular Section at the British Embassy, by email to lapaz.escalations@fco.gov.uk Please note that owing to travel restrictions there is limited consular assistance that the embassy can provide, particularly outside La Paz.
Further information
Further information on coronavirus (COVID-19), including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
